		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I can relate to Stephanie Coontz’s anecdote about cultures where, when husbands find other sexual partners, their wives welcome it [“<a href="/article/5818">The Radical Idea of Marrying for Love</a>,” September 2016]. Without emotional intimacy and good communication between partners, it is more difficult for a woman to experience sexual satisfaction. I appreciated everything about my partner except our frustrating sex life. Thus, when he had two affairs, I was relieved that it took some of the pressure off me.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Name Withheld<br></p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1584">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>In response to the insights of Stephanie Coontz I want to offer the following: the Spanish word for wife is <em>esposa</em>. The word for handcuffs is <em>esposas</em>. Thankfully my Argentine husband and I can joke about this.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">M.J. Vuinovich<br>Lander, Wyoming</p>
					</blockquote>
